OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FBut we should remember, the recession
OL,6,Fthat the UK did, technically, enter
OL,7,Flast year is a very small one compared
OL,8,Fto previous downturns.
OL,10,FGross Domestic Product (GDP) fell by
OL,11,F0.5% between July and December 2023.
OL,12,FDuring the recession of 2008/2009, UK
OL,13,FGDP plunged by 6.4%.
OL,15,FThe recession of 2023 looks shallow,
OL,16,Fit's possible it is already over and
OL,17,Fit may disappear altogether as the
OL,18,FOffice for National Statistics updates
OL,19,Fand revises the data in the months
OL,20,Fahead.
