OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FThe more important point is the
OL,6,Feconomy isn't growing and there are
OL,7,Fgood reasons why that's the case.
OL,9,FAs the chancellor pointed out when I
OL,10,Finterviewed him this morning, the
OL,11,Fpainfully high levels of inflation
OL,12,F(not caused by Rishi Sunak) have
OL,13,Fsqueezed the incomes of households.
OL,15,FHigher interest rates (not set by
OL,16,FRishi Sunak) have left households with
OL,17,Fmortgages poorer.
OL,19,FNeither strike action nor Brexit
OL,20,F(which Rishi Sunak can influence) have
OL,21,Fhelped.
