OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FGDP per head in the UK (that's the
OL,6,Famount our economy produces, divided
OL,7,Fby all the people in the country) is
OL,8,Fthe key measure that determines how
OL,9,Fmuch our incomes rise over time.
OL,11,FThe terrible news is it has been
OL,12,Ffalling for almost two years.
OL,14,FGDP per head in the U.K. is 1.1% lower
OL,15,Fthan it was before COVID (in Q3 2019).
OL,17,FBy contrast, over the same period, GDP
OL,18,Fper head has grown by 2.7% in the
OL,19,FEuropean Union and by 6.5% in the
OL,20,FUnited States.
